# sumo-otel-local project config — copy to .sumo-otel-local.env and edit.
#
# Create it with:  ./sumo-otel-local.sh --init-config   (copies this template)
#
# This file is SOURCED by sumo-otel-local.sh (when present in the working directory),
# so it is plain shell: KEY=value, one per line, no spaces around '='. Values set here
# are applied for the run (loaded with `set -a`), so you can avoid re-answering prompts.
# To ignore this file for a single run, set SUMO_CONFIG_FILE=/dev/null (or point it at
# another path to use a different config).
#
# Copy and uncomment what you need:

# Container runtime: docker or podman (skips the "which runtime?" prompt when both exist).
# CONTAINER_RUNTIME=docker

# KinD cluster name (default: sumo). Used by create, status, and teardown.
# CLUSTER_NAME=sumo

# Pinned sumologic/sumologic Helm chart version (skips the version picker).
# SUMO_CHART_VERSION=5.2.0

# Sumo deployment endpoint. Set this to your org's region so the collector's setup job
# authenticates against the right API — otherwise it defaults to us1 and a non-us1 org
# gets HTTP 401. Accepts a region code (us1, us2, au, ca, de, eu, fed, in, jp, kr) or a
# full API URL (https://api.us2.sumologic.com/api/v1). Blank = prompt, then auto-detect.
# SUMOLOGIC_ENDPOINT=us2

# Skip the pre-flight credential check before install (offline/air-gapped, or the Sumo
# API is firewalled). The chart's setup job still validates server-side.
# SUMO_SKIP_CRED_CHECK=1

# How long `helm --wait` waits for the collector pods to become Ready (default: 10m).
# HELM_WAIT_TIMEOUT=10m

# Helm values file passed to install/output (default: values.yaml if present).
# HELM_VALUES=examples/metrics_interval.yaml

# Podman machine minimums (MiB / vCPUs).
# MIN_MEM_MB=18432
# MIN_CPU=4

# Trust extra CA cert(s) (colon-separated PEM paths) inside every KinD node. For
# networks with a TLS-inspecting proxy (Netskope, Zscaler, etc.): the host trusts the
# proxy's CA, but a freshly created KinD node does not, so image pulls inside the
# cluster fail with "x509: certificate signed by unknown authority" even though pulls
# on the host work fine. Applied on cluster creation/reuse (-i/-n); a no-op when unset.
# EXTRA_CA_CERTS=/path/to/corporate-root-ca.pem

# Run unattended (assume yes, use defaults). Equivalent to -y. Note: destructive
# teardown (-u/-p) still requires the explicit --force flag even with this set.
# ASSUME_YES=yes

# NOT configurable here for safety: --force (destructive auto-confirm) is flag-only.
# Sumo credentials should come from secret storage (macOS Keychain / Linux secret-tool)
# or the SUMOLOGIC_ACCESS_ID / SUMOLOGIC_ACCESS_KEY environment variables — NOT this file
# (a plaintext config on disk). The loader warns if it finds credentials here.
# To save them in the keyring once for unattended installs: `sumo-otel-local.sh --store-credentials`.
# An unattended install (-i -y) fails fast up front if no credentials are available.
